The typewriter was in a moth-eaten case covered with dust. 
Along with it were some typewriter ribbons, a bottle of (dried) ink whitener and even an unfinished manuscript. 
I made a mental note to follow up on that manuscript. 
I brought down the case from the attic and set it on the table. 
As I opened it, a couple of frightened lizards hastily emerged from inside and scrambled for safety. 
I glanced at the name of the typewriter. 
Brother Valiant, 1962. 
In fact, I could fondly recall the names of all these companies, which were quite popular in the 60s and 70s Brother (Japan), Grundig (Germany), Bell & Howell (USA)